{
  "text": "Pyrrolizidine alkaloids are present in distinct plant families that grow worldwide [CITATION_1] , and although they are sporadic in western countries, pyrrolizidine alkaloid poisoning attracts sufficient attention [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Whether SOS is caused by herbal medicines containing pyrrolizidine alkaloids or other factors [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , its pathological process is similar and leads to elevated portal pressure [CITATION_6] . DIPS improved the symptoms of SOS in our study and resulted in better prognosis; however, these results were inconsistent with some previous studies [CITATION_7] . We believe that in the Far East or western countries, regardless of the cause of SOS, the results of our study will be useful for elimination of extrahepatic complications.",
